- 'artists' refers to users who create annotations;
- 'painted' refers to the act of annotating;
- 'high-resolution portraits' refers to faces with a high resolution;
- 'detailed features' refers to the annotation type '6landmarks';
- 'quality surpasses the average quality' indicates that the face quality score is greater than the average face quality score in the dataset.

- 'Active' models are those that are currently in use or under active development;
- 'Completed evaluations' refer to evaluations that have been finished and have a status marked as 'completed';
- 'Normalized metric value' is calculated by dividing the metric value by the metric quality score;
- 'High' accuracy level is defined as a metric value greater than 0.9, otherwise it is 'Low';
- 'Dataset size' is the total size of all images in the dataset, measured in bytes.

- The weighted rating is calculated as (view count * 0.4) + (grayscale image count * 0.3) + (total faces * 0.3);
- The dataset version '1.0' is considered for the rating;
- The access type 'view' is used to count the number of views;
- Grayscale images are identified by the property name 'grayscale'.
